file=Governance/board/custom/strategic-veto/assets/locked-commitments-template.md · [nl:[Business Name] Locked Strategic Commitments — TEMPLATE=> **This is a template, not a strategy.** Nothing here is in force until the operator fills\n> it in and saves it at the path configured in board's config (`locked_commitments_path`).\n> These are the deliberate, time-bound bets the business has locked in — the mid-layer between\n> the constitution (near-permanent never-do's) and config thresholds (tunable numbers).\n> If a commitment is meant to hold for years regardless of strategy, move it to the\n> constitution. If it needs constant exceptions, it isn't locked — retire it.\n\n**Version:** [v0.1]\n**Locked on:** [YYYY-MM-DD]\n**Set by:** [operator, with marcus's strategy process]\n**Next scheduled review:** [YYYY-MM-DD — commitments without a review date rot]\n\n · ar:Amendment Rule=[How commitments change. Example: "Amendments happen only at scheduled strategy reviews, or\noff-cycle with the operator's explicit written approval and a one-line rationale. Board\nenforces; marcus proposes; only the operator locks." A veto's appeal path (a) runs through\nthis rule.]\n\n · c:Commitments=[2–6 is the healthy range. Each needs all four parts — a commitment without a scope test\ncan't be enforced, and one without an expiry can't be trusted.]\n · ### C1 — [Short name]=- **Commitment:** [One sentence, plain language. Example shapes: "Through [date], all new\nproduct work serves [segment/venture]." / "No new ventures launch until [milestone]." /\n"[Function] stays in-house through [date]."]\n- **Why locked:** [One line — the reasoning at lock time, so future reviews judge the reason,\nnot just the rule.]\n- **Scope test:** [How board checks a proposal against it. "A proposal conflicts if it\nredirects [resource/attention/positioning] toward/away from …"]\n- **Expires / reviews:** [Date or triggering milestone.]\n · ### C2 — [Short name]=- **Commitment:**\n- **Why locked:**\n- **Scope test:**\n- **Expires / reviews:**\n · ### C3 — [Short name]=- **Commitment:**\n- **Why locked:**\n- **Scope test:**\n- **Expires / reviews:**\n\n · p:Precedence=[Suggested default: Constitution > these locked commitments > config thresholds\n(fiduciary-guard) > everything else. A proposal must clear all layers independently.]\n · v&a:Veto & Appeal Log Pointer=[Vetoes and their outcomes are recorded in the configured decision log, not here — but note\nthe location so reviews can pull the pattern: repeated vetoes against one commitment mean\ndrift pressure or a stale commitment.]\n